wikipedia_page.main: Captain Arthur Cameron Corbett, 3rd Baron Rowallan (17 December 1919 – 1993), was a British aristocrat most notable for successfully having his second marriage annulled in 1970 on the grounds that his wife April Ashley, a transgender woman, was legally a man. This case is known as Corbett v Corbett.

John Polson Cameron Corbett, 4th Baron Rowallan (born 8 March 1947) is a British hereditary peer.  He is the son of Arthur Corbett, 3rd Baron Rowallan, and Eleanor Mary Boyle. He is usually known as Johnny Corbett or Johnny Rowallan.
